SAW observes an error-in-element inside a recognized Class F fix as an
escaping runtime failure (eval_bool aborts with "Run-time error: at:
index out of bounds"), so no comparable SAW_OBSERVED line can be
printed; executable SAW-vs-Lean error-outcome comparison is not
implemented in the differential harness. The Lean side of the corner
was verified manually 2026-07-16: the emitted artifact's #reduce
observation is `LEAN_OBSERVED: error: at: index out of bounds` —
byte-identical message, agreeing outcome (the Except model surfaces
the same error the lazy evaluator escapes with). The emitted artifact
also still carries the H_prod `by sorry` placeholder (see
fix_classF_eval), which independently blocks parity credit.
